Ontologies

Getty Vocabulary Program ontology

Getty Vocabulary Program ontology (Ontology) VC Definition In use Documentation

The GVP Ontology defines classes, properties and values (skos:Concepts) used in GVP LOD. As of version 3.0, it is complete regarding AAT, TGN and ULAN, and will be extended in time with more elements needed for other GVP vocabularies (CONA). It uses the SKOS, SKOS-XL, ISO 25964; DC, DCT, BIBO, FOAF, BIO, Schema, PROV, WGS84 ontologies, but we import only the first 3

AdminPlaceConcept (OWL Class) Definition In use

Place defined by administrative boundaries and conditions, including inhabited places, nations, and empires. Used in TGN only. Example: Burgundy region in France (TGN)

Definition

The URI of this class is http://vocab.getty.edu/ontology#AdminPlaceConcept

This class is a sub class of skos:Concept Subject

In use

This class is defined by Getty Vocabulary Program ontology

Biography (OWL Class) Definition In use

Biography of a ULAN agent (schema:Person|Organization). Depending on the agent, has these fields: - schema:description: one-line-biography - gvp:estStart - schema:birthPlace | foundationLocation, pointing to TGN - gvp:estEnd - schema:deathPlace | dissolutionLocation, pointing to TGN - schema:gender, pointing to AAT (male, female, other) - dct:contributor The fields of the preferred biogrpahy are also available in the agent.

Definition

The URI of this class is http://vocab.getty.edu/ontology#Biography

In use

This class is defined by Getty Vocabulary Program ontology

This class is used in biography biographyNonPreferred biographyPreferred

Concept (OWL Class) Definition In use

Proper concept. Used in AAT only; TGN & ULAN have their own, e.g. gvp:PhysPlaceConcept & gvp:PersonConcept. Used for indexing and cataloguing. Example: rhyta (AAT)

GroupConcept (OWL Class) Definition In use

Two or more people who generally worked together to collectively create art. Not necessarily legally incorporated. A family of artists may be considered a "corporate body". Corresponds to crm:E74_Group, not its subclass crm:E40_Legal_Body. Example: 500356337 Albrecht Duerer Workshop (ULAN)

ObsoleteSubject (OWL Class) Definition In use
